The paper focuses on the aesthetic appeal and usability of graph drawings, which falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of different layout algorithms for trees and sparse graphs suggests a focus on data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the task of performing furthest-pair or shortest-path tasks on the drawings suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
